Package: microscapeR
Title: Downstream Analysis Tools for Amplicon Sequencing Data
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: person("R. Eric", "Collins", email="recollins@alaska.edu",
                   role=c("cre","aut"))
Description: Provides downstream analysis tools for amplicon sequencing
    data produced by DADA2. Includes sequence table quality filtering,
    MIMARKS metadata loading, taxonomic renormalization, phylogenetic tree
    construction, Bray-Curtis ordination with t-SNE, and SparCC-style
    correlation network analysis. Designed as a companion to the dada2
    Bioconductor package and the Python microscape package.
License: BSD_3_clause + file LICENSE
Depends: R (>= 4.4)
Imports: data.table, ape, Biostrings, DECIPHER, stats, utils
Suggests: testthat (>= 3.0), BiocStyle, knitr, rmarkdown, dada2, Rtsne
biocViews: Sequencing, Microbiome, Metagenomics, Clustering, Visualization
URL: https://github.com/rec3141/microscapeR
BugReports: https://github.com/rec3141/microscapeR/issues
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Encoding: UTF-8
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
